Class Distributor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • teetime.framework.AbstractStage
      • teetime.framework.AbstractConsumerStage<T>
        • teetime.stage.basic.distributor.Distributor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of both the input and output ports
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DynamicDistributor

    public class Distributor<T>
extends AbstractConsumerStage<T>
    New output ports can be created by calling getNewOutputPort().
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Christian Wulf, Nelson Tavares de Sousa
    Stage output:
    The incoming element will be passed to output ports, which are selected by a strategy.
